==English==

===Etymology===
Shortened form of “of the clock” or “on the clock”, that is, “according to the clock”.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-o'clock.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adverb===
{{en-adv|pos=[[o']][[clock]]|-}}

# {{context|modifying a numeral, one to twelve}} {{non-gloss definition|In conjunction with a numeral, indicates the [[time]] within a twelve hour period ([[midnight]] to [[noon]] or noon to midnight), specifically the time when the hour hand of a clock points precisely to the symbol or marking corresponding to the designated numeral.}}
#: ''We are expected to be there at six '''o'clock''' in the morning!''
#: ''It is two '''o'clock'''.
#: ''What '''o'clock''' is it?'' [uncommon]
